&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Boston-based company Piaggio Fast Forward Inc. (PFF) was founded in 2015 by the Piaggio Group (the Italian manufacturer that created the iconic Vespa scooter). We are on a mission to build technology products that move the way that people move. To bring products to market today, PFF is solving the problem of robotic interaction with people in dynamically changing environments. We’re innovators, neighbors, and creators with a passion for local living and pushing the limits on urban transportation. We support a sustainable mobility ecology with healthy lifestyles and social connectivity available to all, regardless of age or abilities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PFF has two branches specializing in Advanced Rider Assistance Systems present on over 20,000 motorbikes and scooters such as Piaggio MP3, Moto Guzzi Stelvio and Moto Guzzi Mandello; and on collaborative mobile robots.&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SSJf8B1-ve0&quot;&gt;PFF kilo&lt;/a&gt; - our latest solution - is a collaborative mobile robot (CMR) designed to augment human performance eliminating physical pushing and pulling - developed for dynamic unmapped environments where full automation is not a fit.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PFF is looking for candidates for our robotics sales team with a strong commercial background in robotics and automation in the warehouse, manufacturing and logistics sectors. The product you will become expert on and will commercialize is &lt;strong&gt;PFF kilo&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As PFF’s &lt;strong&gt;Business Development Leader&lt;/strong&gt;, you are driven by strong commercial acumen and have a background in building sales engines from the ground up. This manager level role reports to the SVP of Sales and will act as an executional right hand who excels at translating strategy into motion and driving disciplined execution. The ideal candidate combines tactical rigor, industry relationships, and executional focus. You know how to run the machine, keep teams aligned, and turn vision into measurable progress. This role is built for an operator who thrives in a high‑velocity environment and amplifies the impact of a strategically oriented SVP by owning the day‑to‑day commercial rhythm of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and define target customers, new markets, and early adopters segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with SVP, Sales to implement, track, and share in the success of the sales team as well as operating as an individual contributor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promotion and outreach to new prospects through inbound leads and cold calling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive outbound prospecting, qualification, and opportunity creation across manufacturing, warehouse, and hyper scale data centers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting on weekly sales activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead closure efforts on high-value opportunities; Support the SVP in executive-level negotiations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in most important industry trade show events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translates the SVP’s strategic direction into actionable plans, timelines, and measurable outcomes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel between 40 - 70 % - US / North America&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular in person meetings at our Boston HQ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Leverage the company&#39;s CRM (HubSpot) and lead generation tool for new and existing leads, best practices for account management, opportunity management, sales reports, contracts. Rollout programs and templates to simplify capture of market data and optimization of sales resource time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, refine and implement targeting approach to drive new customer acquisition&a

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Boston-based company Piaggio Fast Forward Inc. (PFF) was founded in 2015 by the Piaggio Group (the Italian manufacturer that created the iconic Vespa scooter). We are on a mission to build technology products that move the way that people move. In order to bring products to market today, PFF is solving the problem of robotic interaction with people in dynamically changing environments. We’re innovators, neighbors and creators with a passion for local living and pushing the limits on urban and business transportation . We support a sustainable mobility ecology with healthy lifestyles, social connectivity and productive work environments available to all, regardless of age or abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Piaggio Fast Forward (PFF) is seeking a highly technical DevOps Engineer to help build and scale the cloud, automation, and deployment infrastructure powering gita®, kilo® , our automotive products and future PFF products. You’ll work at the intersection of software, infrastructure, and automation—owning CI/CD pipelines, AWS environments, and Infrastructure‑as‑Code while enabling engineering teams to ship reliable software at speed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect, implement, and maintain AWS cloud infrastructure with a focus on scalability, security, and automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage Infrastructure‑as‑Code using Terraform (modules, workspaces, state management, reusable patterns)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and optimize GitHub (repos, branching strategies, GitHub Actions, integrations, permissions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, maintain, and extend Jenkins CI/CD pipelines for automated builds, testing, and deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop automation to streamline development workflows, environment provisioning, and release processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement containerized environments using Docker and AWS container services (ECS/EKS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform system performance tuning, load testing, and reliability analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and troubleshoot production and staging environments using AWS native tools and open‑source observability stacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Software, QA, and Operations teams to improve deployment velocity and system resilience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document infrastructure, pipelines, and operational processes for internal engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;What you Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of hands‑on DevOps engineering experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise with AWS (IAM, EC2, VPC, S3, CloudWatch, ECS/EKS, Lambda, CloudFormation)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency with Terraform (IaC best practices, modular design, automation workflows)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience configuring and managing GitHub at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience building and maintaining Jenkins CI/CD pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Linux fundamentals and shell scripting skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Docker and container orchestration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Java, C/C++, or Python build environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with NoSQL databases such as MongoDB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of open‑source tooling and automation frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in Agile/Scrum environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and ability to collaborate across engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Experience with Ansible, Puppet, or Chef; embedded build systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful applicants will be asked to show proof that they can legally work in the U.S&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
